she then placed the body in a plastic bag and dropped it in the yard of a neighbor. District Attorney <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzgerald </PERSON> said in his closing arguments that the physical evidence, including other cut and stab marks on the infant's body, showed the girl really was trying to kill the baby. `` Nice people do bad things; sometimes they do crimes,'' <PERSON> Fitzgerald </PERSON> said. But defense attorney <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Kaminski </PERSON> said the prosecution managed to prove only that the girl had a baby. `` Where is the evidence of death after life?'' he asked. `` As horrible as it is, this is not a murder.'' He conceded that `` everything she did was bad news'' but added his client did not intend to kill the boy. He said prosecution testimony had `` glaring ommissions'' and that the entire prosecution was based on `` manipulation and speculation.''
